Text.string: Maliwan's set up a butt-load of bases between us and the Vault. This is exactly why I tried to keep Nekrotafeyo secret in the first place, but I guess that bird's out of its cage. You gotta get the last Key. I hid it near the Vault.
There's a bridge that leads to Vault-side. Head there, and good luck with Maliwan.
Yeah, Leda. She died, though.
I am so sorry for your loss.||—Yesss.
Vault Hunter. If you get the chance, please get Typhon DeLeon's autograph for me. And a lock of his hair. For research purposes.

I've been waiting for this a long time, Vault Hunter. This is General Daniel Traunt, and you're the feckless SOB who killed my little brother Samuel on Athenas. Well, Tyreen Calypso said you'd show up sooner or later. I taught Sammy how to fight, but you taught him how to die. And now I'm gonna teach YOU!||—How... how to die. Just to be clear. Traunt!
Another Traunt? Interesting. Iron Bear would like to meet him.
Great, another Traunt. My other fist was getting jealous.
Another of the Traunt clan. This one must be the alpha.
Another Traunt! Boy, that brings me back. Good times.
Sure are a lot of Maliwans here. You better send 'em packin', Vault Hunter.
Holy granoli, what a battle! You're amazing!
Ha! Take that, you putzes!
Lonely baloney! You're a natural!
Nice fighting, Vault Hunter! I'm impressed.

I'll bet when you saw me you said to yourself, “THAT's the First Vault Hunter? This guy? Ha!” People have been underestimating me my whole life. But like I always say: heroes come in all shapes and sizes!
Pah! Those were just scrubs. Let's see how you square up against my elites!
You ain't gettin' through that force-field unless you take out the generator on the other side! Like I always say: when you're in mud, find some higher ground!
There ya go. Now blast that generator, Vault Hunter!
All right! The bridge to Vault-side is just ahead.
Suck on my big brother-sized balls, Vault Hunter. Trauuuunt!
He destroyed the bridge! What a schmendrick. Don't worry—there's another way to Vault-side, but it ain't gonna be easy.
You can't run, Vault Hunter! Well, y-you can, but I'll find you, heh-heh! In my ship. To be clear. It's got great vantage. Its vantage is my greatest advantage!
Your journey ends here, Vault Hunter. I'm gonna END you, for my name is Daniel Traunt!
This one's for my little brother Sammy! Trauuuuuuunt!
It's nice to have some company for a change. Haven't had anyone human to talk to for years. See, I crash-landed decades ago. I've been marooned here ever since.
Mmm, soft serve sounds good. Wonder what flavors they have in hell.
I would kill him again if I got some soft serve. Just saying.
He is dead. Also, I wonder how I would process this “soft serve”.
I could go for some soft serve. Cherry-vanilla all the way, boyo.
That path'll lead straight to the Vault! That's where I hid the Key. Don't worry, I'll stand guard outside the machine and keep the other Keys safe!
Now get your heroic keister moving! We've got a universe to save!
You made it! Now, there's a big-ass Eridian temple up ahead. That's your ticket to the Vault.
Typhon, how did you even find Nekrotafeyo?
Yeah, Maya always said it was just a story.

Ha! So did everyone! Except my wife Leda. She figured it out. After we got married on Pandora, we left to find Nekrotafeyo for our honeymoon. Well, we ended up crash-landing! See, I put the ship on autopilot while we got busy. That's on me. And so was she! Anywho, the ship was kaput. Comm link was kaput. But we didn't care. We were in love!

Leda, she was whip-smart. And smart with the whip. Boy, did THAT come in handy on our honeymoon! After we opened the Vault, that's when the REAL ACTION began. Skag on skag. Key and hook! The double Calvin! Nine months later, well... there's only one thing in life that happens nine months later.
For awhile, we were one happy family. Then Leda, she... well, she died. And I had to raise the kids alone. I thought opening a Vault would be the hardest thing I'd ever do. Hoh-oh, was I wrong!

The boy, he got sick all the time. And my daughter talked circles around me! Only time they'd sit still was to hear about my adventures. Killing monsters, opening Vaults, being a hero—they couldn't get enough!

I had to get real creative to survive here. You wanna hear my secret? Get this: I'm really smart. I always say, smart's good. Small's good, too! You can fit in places. And ugly's the best. People don't wanna look at ya! Perfect for sneakin'!
I filled their heads with all sorts of stories. Even told 'em about the Great Vault... heh, that was a mistake! A story can be a dangerous thing in the wrong hands.
The temple's just up ahead! Those Maliwan must want that Vault bad. Wonder if they know I already opened the sucker years ago.
Maliwan has the entire place fortified! But the only way to the Vault is the elevator inside! So, you're gonna have to send those putzes packing.
Wooo, you fight GOOD! This generation of Vault Hunters, I tell ya, must be somethin' in the water! There's an elevator you can take up to the Vault. I know how it works.
Yup, there's your problem. Elevator's missing two crystals. Everything runs on crystals around here. Ooh! Looks like one's over there.
Go ahead and put it in the statue's hands. Like an offering.
Nice. Wonder where that other crystal is, though.
Attention, high command. I have located the final crystal!
General Traunt, do you copy? Should I proceed to the Vault, or... ah, crap, it's a Vault Hunter!
The other crystal! Offer it to that statue!
And I do my share of sneakin'! Since Maliwan showed up, I've been nabbin' tech and listenin' in on their ECHOs. Great products, but piss-poor security... if you're smart!
Huh, still not workin'. Right, you've got to align the statues. Looks like Maliwan rigged up some sorta device to turn 'em.
Just take that elevator straight to the Vault. Been a long time since anyone's been in there.
Oh, almost forgot. Me and Leda? We made it on the elevator too. Right where you're standin'! Ha!
So, you made it to Nekrotafeyo. [clapping] Slow clap. 'Cause you're slow. Always playing catch-up, aren't ya? All that's left on that planet is dust and demons. Trust me.
Hurry, Vault Hunter. The Key's just up ahead.
You're wasting your time. The Destroyer's almost here, and when I consume it, I'm gonna be a god. I know you're listening, Dad. Are you proud of your little girl?
Tyreen... starlight...
Uh, what?

You weren't gonna tell them, were you, Dad? Oops! Well, Vault Thief, guess who taught us everything we needed to know to take this galaxy apart piece by piece? Typhon DeLeon. The First Vault Hunter. Oh, Dad, by the way? Troy's dead. Your friend there killed him. So... have fun with that.
Vault Hunter, the Guardians know you're here. Fight 'em off. We'll talk after.
Anyway, keep heading towards the bridge. I'm gonna check in with your people and let 'em know what's up.
Get rid of those guardians, Vault Hunter. Then we can grab the Key.
At the Vault, Typhon. No key in sight.
I'm at the Vault, Typhon. Don't see a key, though.
I've reached the Vault, Typhon. But the Key is missing.
Reached the Vault, T-money. But don't see the Key.
You think I'd just leave the Key lyin' around? I hid it. There's a weird-looking Eridian device over there. Activate it, and I'll join ya. And then we'll have our talk.
Hate those things. Ugh.
Me and Leda beat that Vault Monster together. Heh. Let's go pay her a visit.
Come on, Vault Hunter. Not far now.
This way, Vault Hunter.
Typhon... about Troy.
Typhon. So... about Troy.
Typhon. We should discuss Troy.
Uh, Typhon. The thing with Troy...
Yeah... listen. I know what's been goin' on out there. Troy and Tyreen, my kids, well... they became monsters. No other way to say it. And you're a Vault Hunter. You kill monsters. Simple as that.
Typhon... why didn't you tell us the Calypsos were your children?
Hey, just got a... rambling message from Typhon DeLeon, something about a machine and another Vault Key. He seems to like you. Do us proud, killer.
I wanted to, and I should've... but I couldn't find the words. How my kids ended up, that's on me. And I might've doomed the whole universe, but I can't let that be how my story ends.
The Key, it's with her. She watches over it.
Not in her grave, Vault Hunter. The headstone! Gah! Guess I could've been clearer. I got it, I got it!
Okay! Whew. That's done. Take the Key.
Right. Now to the Vault. Like I said, me and Leda already killed the monster, but there's somethin' you gotta see.

When me and Leda first saw Troy and Tyreen's tattoos, we knew we had to protect 'em. Sirens, hoo! The rarest thing in the universe, and there were two of 'em right in our arms. The only way to keep 'em safe was to stay here. Forever.
But that didn't work out so well. I might've been a first-rate adventurer, but I was a third-rate pops. If you don't raise your kids right, what kinda hero are you?
Listen. What comes next, it ain't gonna be easy. We got one shot. But I gotta fix this. For Leda.
So... me and Leda... we sorta already looted the place. But I got somethin' for ya.
Okay, go on. Get your reward. You earned it.
Hey, Vault Hunter. Vaughn says Pandora's shaking like an ice skag with fever dreams. No word from Tyreen, but we've got your back—which is my preferred view of ya, as you know!
Hahaha! Just joshin' ya. Here, have this!
Give it a go, Vault Hunter. I've never been inside the machine, but I'm gonna guess we're gonna need all the firepower we can get our hands on.
Guess ya don't need me anymore... Heh heh.
You check in with your people, I'll head to the machine. And hey, from one Vault Hunter to another... thanks. I just hope we still have time to fix things.
Huh. Back in my day, the thugs would shut down a force-field instead of jumping over it. Looks like you'll have to take out the generator on the other side.
Wait—you've got kids, Typhon?
Yeah... two of 'em.
Looks like Maliwan never got beyond the first floor of the temple. Ha! Chumps.
Look, I'm not sayin' I'm glad my boy's dead, but at least he can't hurt people no more.

After their mother died, I was so scared I'd lose them too. So I kept 'em here. I thought they'd be happy. But they kept staring up at that sky, full of stars they'd never reach. To me, this planet was enough! The reward at the end of my hunt. To them, it was just a cage.
So, Typhon. May I call you Typhon? Is there a... Mrs. DeLeon?
Boy, this brings me back! Been avoiding this place a long time.
